> Tasks must be executable, verifiable, and traceable.

## Task Writing Rules

- Each task should do one thing only
- A single task should ideally fit within half a day to one day
- Every task must link to requirement / design / test
- Tasks with no traceability should not enter development
- Task descriptions should be action-oriented, such as “implement X and add Y tests”, not vague phrases like “improve experience”

## Task Template

```text
- [ ] T-001 [Task description]
  - Requirement: FR-001
  - Design: DES-001
  - Test: TEST-001
  - Output: [code / docs / script]
  - Depends on: [none or task ID]
```

